## 6 Conclusion

This paper reveals the surprisingly close relationship between the powerful Mamba and subpar linear attention Transformer, shedding some light on Mamba's superiority and success. We rephrase Mamba as a variant of linear attention Transformer and identify its six major special designs: input gate, forget gate, shortcut, no attention normalization, single-head and modified block design. Empirical validation shows that the forget gate and block design largely enhance performance, while the other distinctions offer marginal contributions or impair model performance. Based on our findings, we propose our Mamba-Inspired Linear Attention (MILA) model by incorporating the merits of these two key designs into linear attention. MILA surpasses various vision Mamba models across multiple tasks, while maintaining parallel computation and high inference speed.

